numbers

Class PrimeNumberGenerator

  • java.lang.Object
    • numbers.PrimeNumberGenerator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Resetable, ResetableIterator<java.lang.Long>, java.util.Iterator<java.lang.Long>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BufferedPrimeNumberGenerator

    public class PrimeNumberGenerator
extends java.lang.Object
implements ResetableIterator<java.lang.Long>
    The PrimeNumberGenerator generates prime numbers and can be used in a for loop. This Generator is defaulted to see 1 not as a prime number.
    Since:
    19-8-2014
    Version:
    20-8-2014
    Author:
    stefanboodt
    See Also:
    BufferedPrimeNumberGenerator, ResetableIterator

      • reset

        public void reset()
        Description copied from interface: Resetable
        Resets the resetable so it can be used again from scratch. That is the class is reset so that it is entirely recreated with the same variables as the first time, while maintaining the old references. It is practical for when the original parameters are no longer in existance, but you like to use the old resetable.
        Specified by:
        reset in interface Resetable
